1
00:01:13,700 --> 00:01:19,100
Have you ever wondered
how Nature gets its glow?

2
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:26,100
Who gives it light and colour as the
seasons come and go?

3
00:01:26,300 --> 00:01:31,700
Who helps all creatures great and small...

4
00:01:31,800 --> 00:01:36,400
to walk, to swim, to fly?

5
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:40,900
Who crafts such tiny details?

6
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:46,400
You might see them if you try...

7
00:01:46,700 --> 00:01:51,300
For it's all the work of fairies, but
they stay well out of sight...

8
00:01:57,300 --> 00:02:03,500
The first time that a baby laughs, a fairy's
life takes flight...

9
00:02:03,500 --> 00:02:07,400
When the moon comes up to shine her face...

10
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:10,500
and the birds are fast asleep...

11
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:14,500
And the mountains hang from every post,

12
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:17,000
The fairies leave their keep!

13
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:21,000
They join their hands and sing their songs,

14
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:25,400
The mariners all can hear!

15
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:29,300
In the springtime when the earth is new,

16
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:31,800
The fairies might draw near!

17
00:02:32,600 --> 00:02:36,300
The fairies might draw near!

18
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:44,800
TINKER BELL

19
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:11,900
- Hello!
- Hello?

20
00:04:12,100 --> 00:04:16,300
Queen Clarion!

21
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:31,500
Born of laughter, clothed in cheer,
Happiness has brought you here!

22
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:35,500
Welcome to Pixie Hollow!

23
00:04:35,500 --> 00:04:38,800
- I trust you found your way alright!
- I... think so.

24
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:46,200
Now let's see about those wings!

25
00:05:30,300 --> 00:05:34,700
They will help you find your talent, little one.

26
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:39,000
- But how will I know which one is...
- You'll know!

27
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:20,900
I've never seen one glow that much before!
Even for Vidia!

28
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:26,000
You know, I do believe you're right! The little
lazy tod might be a very rare talent indeed!

29
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:39,400
Come forward, Tinker fairies and welcome...

30
00:07:39,500 --> 00:07:43,500
the newest member of your talent kin... Tinker Bell!

31
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:50,000
- I'm glad we had a bath today!
- Coming through!

32
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:54,300
Make way for Tinkers! Hy-dy high,
hy-dy how, Miss Bell!

33
00:07:54,300 --> 00:07:58,900
- I'm Clank!
- Clank, say it, don't spray it!

34
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,900
Amphilious T. Cattletree esquire, at your service!

35
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:08,000
- Pleased to make your acquaintance!
- Oh, boo... He's Boble, I'm Clank!

36
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:11,500
Clank, Boble!

37
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:15,000
We're pleased as a pair of perfectly polished
pots you're here!

38
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,800
Aaa... me, too!

39
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:23,800
Come on, miss Bell, there's so much to show you!

40
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:27,800
You've arrived at a most wonderous and
glorious time!

41
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:31,900
- Really? Why?
- It's almost time for the changing of the seasons!

42
00:08:32,200 --> 00:08:39,200
You see, here in Pixie Hollow, there are
different realms for every time of year!

43
00:08:39,300 --> 00:08:43,700
There's one up ahead!

44
00:08:43,700 --> 00:08:47,700
Winter Woods, it's always cold here!

45
00:08:47,700 --> 00:08:50,800
Look there! Snowflake and Frost fairies
returning home...

46
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,200
for some well-deserved rest!

47
00:08:54,300 --> 00:08:57,900
We've just finished bringing winter to the world.

48
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:01,600
It's the up season for Autumn fairies, too.

49
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:06,400
Always practicing their perfect shade of amber, hey.

50
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:09,900
And the fairies of Summer still have plenty
of time to get ready!

51
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:14,700
Not as much as the Autumn fairies, of course, because...

52
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:19,100
Yes, Clank, because right now fairies of every
talent are preparing for my favorite season,

53
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:24,000
Springtime.

54
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:29,300
Get low, get low, little sproutings and dig.

55
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:37,200
- Hello, there!
- Come on, miss Bell, you've got to see where we live.

56
00:09:45,200 --> 00:09:49,000
Welcome to Tinker's Nuke!

57
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,900
Come on, there's so much to show you.

58
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:31,400
Oh, cute.

59
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:35,400
Just taking some supplies down to the workshop.

60
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:39,300
Let her go.

61
00:10:39,600 --> 00:10:43,500
Watch out for falling maple seeds!

62
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:50,400
Wow.

63
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:04,000
- And over here is where most of us live!
- There's your house, Tinker Bell!

64
00:11:09,300 --> 00:11:14,500
- Ah, it's mine?
- Sure is.

65
00:11:14,500 --> 00:11:18,400
We were hoping that your arrival would be
of one of us, so we got the place all ready.

66
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:22,500
- We rounded up some work clothes!
- We did not know your size!

67
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:25,700
- Our apologies.
- They might be too big!

68
00:11:25,800 --> 00:11:31,000
- That's only because you're so tiny.
- Please come on down to the workshop when you're ready.

69
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:36,400
- Fairy Mary will want to meet you.
- Good bye!

70
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:29,700
- Stop!
- What?

71
00:12:29,700 --> 00:12:33,500
Clank, I told you to take a seven.

72
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:37,800
- You said five!
- I said a seven!

73
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:41,800
- Pretty!
- So...

74
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:46,800
Pretty.

75
00:12:46,900 --> 00:12:51,400
- Who's that then?
- It's Tinker Bell, you snail brain!

76
00:12:51,500 --> 00:12:55,700
Wow, everyone seems so busy!

77
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:59,000
Spring won't spring itself.

78
00:12:59,100 --> 00:13:02,800
Indeed my bellowing buddy and we Tinkers are
a big part of it.

79
00:13:02,900 --> 00:13:07,700
Allow us to elucidate, miss Bell!

80
00:13:07,900 --> 00:13:11,300
- We fiddle and fix.
- We craft and create.

81
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:14,300
- We carve acorn buckets.
- To hold flower paints.

82
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,800
- With saddles and saches.
- For birdies, you see.

83
00:13:16,900 --> 00:13:20,000
- We make baskets and bushels.
- To carry the seeds.

84
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:23,600
- We're preparing for spring.
- We do all these and more.

85
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:25,900
- Yes!
- Because being a Tinker is never a bore.

86
00:13:25,900 --> 00:13:31,300
- That was great.
- So you see, miss Bell, we help fairies
of every talent with our creations.

87
00:13:31,500 --> 00:13:36,500
Unfortunately, all those fairies are out of luck this year!

88
00:13:36,500 --> 00:13:40,000
Unless we can actually deliver these things to them!

89
00:13:40,300 --> 00:13:45,400
- The wagon repairs are finished, I trust?
- Yes, Fairy Mary.

90
00:13:45,500 --> 00:13:50,100
- They're top shaped.
- No wheel is missing whatsoever.

91
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:53,200
Then let's see it!

92
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:58,700
- Define seeing actually!
- With your eyes!

93
00:13:58,800 --> 00:14:02,000
- You have to meet Tinker Bell!
- What?

94
00:14:02,100 --> 00:14:05,900
- Who?
- She's new, Fairy Mary.

95
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:10,200
- Nice to meet you!
- Oh, rapture! A new charge on whom we can
lavish all our...

96
00:14:10,400 --> 00:14:13,900
tinkering wisdom and expertise!

97
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:18,400
Let me see those hands! Oh, so dainty!

98
00:14:18,500 --> 00:14:22,000
Don't worry, dear! We'll build up those
Tinker muscles in no time!

99
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:26,600
- Ok!
- Now, boys, the deliveries!

100
00:14:26,700 --> 00:14:31,000
We're on it! As a matter of fact, we're
heading out right this second!

101
00:14:31,300 --> 00:14:36,300
- But we've only got one wheel.
- What was that?

102
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:40,200
- Nothing really, Clank was just asking...
- If...

103
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:44,400
- I can go as well.
- Yes!

104
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:48,400
- I wondered that.
- That's exactly what he was saying!

105
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:52,400
Very well, get on with it, then!

106
00:14:54,900 --> 00:14:58,300
Slow down, Cheese. I can't keep up!

107
00:14:58,800 --> 00:15:02,800
- The mouse's name is Cheese?
- It must be! He always comes when we yell it!

108
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:35,000
Sprinting thistles!

109
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:56,100
Aaa!

110
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:14,200
Easy! Easy, boy!

111
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:18,700
It's alright, Fawn's got you!

112
00:16:18,800 --> 00:16:22,800
Easy, easy girl, it's alright, Silvermist's got you!

113
00:16:22,800 --> 00:16:25,800
- Oh, you alright, sugar cake?
- Be careful, Rosetta, she may faint!

114
00:16:25,800 --> 00:16:30,700
- Elevate her legs!
- No, wait, I mean her head.

115
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:35,700
Wait, wait, if she's red, raise the head,
if she's pale, raise the tail.

116
00:16:35,800 --> 00:16:38,900
- Does she look pale or red?
- She looks squished!

117
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:42,000
- Sorry.
- Here, let me, rain drop! So...

118
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:45,400
what happened to you, anyway?

119
00:16:45,500 --> 00:16:48,500
- Well...
- It was sprinting thistles!

120
00:16:48,500 --> 00:16:51,500
Those weeds are an absolute mess! Always trapping
things, poking people in the petunia!

121
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:54,900
Gather around, ladies!

122
00:16:55,000 --> 00:17:01,600
We've brought some selections from the new
spring line of Tinkers' specialities!

123
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,900
- Alright!
- Show us!

124
00:17:04,400 --> 00:17:06,900
- Your rainbow tubes, Iridessa!
- Finally!

125
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,300
Silvermist, could you help me?

126
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,000
- Wow, what are you going to do with that?
- I'm gonna take it to the Mainland.

127
00:17:31,100 --> 00:17:35,800
- What's the Mainland?
- It's where we are going to change winter to spring.

128
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,800
The seasons change all the time there.

129
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:43,500
I'll get to apply my artistic sensibilities.

130
00:17:43,500 --> 00:17:47,400
And I'll have breakfast ready for all the
little fuzzies coming out of hibernation.

131
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:51,600
We just follow the second star...

132
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:53,900
We ride the breeze, we follow the waves...

133
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:58,000
- All the way across the sea.
- Then, there it is.

134
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:01,800
Wow! The Mainland sounds flitterific!

135
00:18:04,900 --> 00:18:09,300
Yes, the glamorous lives of the Nature talent fairies!

136
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:13,700
- We'd love to stay and chat...
- But we Tinkers have real work to do!

137
00:18:13,700 --> 00:18:18,500
We know. Don't we like that!

138
00:18:18,500 --> 00:18:22,300
- Nice to meet you all.
- You, too! Bye! Later!

139
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:29,000
Right, here we are... a pretty
large order of pollen pots for...

140
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:47,400
- The last thing is...
- Is it ok if I just catch up with you later?

141
00:18:47,500 --> 00:18:52,300
- I suppose.
- Can you find your way back?

142
00:18:52,500 --> 00:18:56,100
Yeah, yeah, sure I can.

143
00:18:56,300 --> 00:18:59,500
- Alright then.
- Just be careful!

144
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:05,800
Hi, there... sorry...

145
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:10,800
Vidia, right?

146
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:18,800
We didn't officially meet. I'm Tinker Bell.

147
00:19:19,300 --> 00:19:24,100
- Oh, yes, the new girl.
- That's right.

148
00:19:24,200 --> 00:19:29,700
- So, what's your talent?
- What do you think it is?

149
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:33,800
You're a poleniser?

150
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,800
Polenator? Polen-picker? Polenflucker?

151
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:41,200
I am a fast flying fairy. A true rare talent.

152
00:19:41,100 --> 00:19:44,000
And this is but a small part of what I do.

153
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:49,400
I make breezes in the summer. I blow down leaves
in the fall. My winds even brought you here, dear.

154
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:54,600
Fairies of every talent depend on me.

155
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,300
- Hey, that's just like what I do.
- Excuse me?

156
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:00,800
I mean Tinkers help fairies of every talent, too, so...

157
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:04,200
We're kind of the same, you know?

158
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:08,900
Sweetie, I make forces of Nature.

159
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:12,200
You make pots and kettles.

160
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:16,500
I work up in the sky and you work down in a ditch.

161
00:20:16,700 --> 00:20:19,300
- Hey!
- Don't get me wrong, sunshine!

162
00:20:19,500 --> 00:20:23,000
Being a tinker is really swell and all,
but I wouldn't go...

163
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:27,200
around bragging about your talent! It's
not like spring depends on you!

164
00:20:27,300 --> 00:20:30,900
Of course it does! And when I go to the Mainland,
I'll prove just how important we are!

165
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:35,800
- When who goes to the Mainland?
- Me, of course!

166
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:40,500
- For spring!
- Oh, of course!

167
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:43,400
- You'll prove it, huh?
- Yes, I will..

168
00:20:43,500 --> 00:20:46,700
Well, I for one, am looking forward to that.

169
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:50,000
Excuse me.

170
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:54,700
No, excuse me.

171
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:59,500
Mine is a rare talent!

172
00:20:59,500 --> 00:21:02,700
A!

173
00:21:02,800 --> 00:21:06,700
Don't tell me Tinkers don't matter.

174
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:10,500
I'll show her what rare talent really is when I'll...

175
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:45,900
- Hey, Tink. What you got there?
- Oh, hi.

176
00:22:45,900 --> 00:22:50,500
- I don't know, I just found them.
- Lost things.

177
00:22:50,500 --> 00:22:53,000
Uuu, lost things!

178
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:57,500
Hey, stuff gets lost and washes up on
Neverland from day to day.

179
00:22:57,600 --> 00:23:00,400
- You know, from the Mainland.
- These come from the Mainland?

180
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:03,400
That place sounds more fascinating all the time.

181
00:23:03,400 --> 00:23:07,300
Fairy potions, checked! Polen pots, checked!

182
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:10,400
Lost things, checked!

183
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:13,000
Lost things? Why are you fiddling with that junk?

184
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:17,800
They were just so... unusual!

185
00:23:17,900 --> 00:23:21,600
You should not be wasting your time with that rubbish.

186
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:25,700
And I won't have it cluttering up my workshop.

187
00:23:25,700 --> 00:23:30,400
And as for you two... No more
dilly-dallying around!

188
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:34,500
And don't forget about the queen's
review tonight. Goodness!

189
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:39,300
There's still so much to be done! Thank you!

190
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:43,200
Sorry about your trinkets, miss Bell.

191
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:46,400
Well, we best be getting ready for the review, anyway.

192
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:50,200
- What is the queen's review?
- You see, the queen...

193
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:53,600
is going to review all the preparations for spring.

194
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:57,800
- It is a good time for us Tinkers to show what we can do, hey?
- Indeed!

195
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:01,300
- Really?
- Like me, I can be a wheel!

196
00:24:01,300 --> 00:24:04,200
Perfect.

197
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:07,500
That's my chance.

198
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:07,000
Ok, everybody, turn! Ready for the phase code over here!

199
00:25:16,200 --> 00:25:19,200
A, splendid, splendid.

200
00:25:19,300 --> 00:25:21,800
There's plenty of time before the queen arrives.

201
00:25:21,800 --> 00:25:26,400
- A! It's the queen!
- What? She's here? Now?

202
00:25:26,500 --> 00:25:30,800
Play, Music fairies.

203
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:34,600
Play.

204
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:47,300
Queen Clarion, your illustriousness,
as minister pf spring.

205
00:25:47,300 --> 00:25:50,800
I welcome you to Springtime Square.

206
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:56,300
- What? No fireworks, minister?
- A, well, that could be arranged!

207
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:59,500
- Light fairies, light fairies.
- I'm teasing you.

208
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:04,000
You always make such a fuss and everything
turns out wonderfully.

209
00:26:07,800 --> 00:26:11,000
Well, I think that you'll find that
we have things well in hand.

210
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:14,500
The ever-blossom blooms will be ready to
bring spring to the Mainland.

211
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:17,700
Music to my ears.

212
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:20,900
I know you all put in months of practice
and preparation.

213
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:23,800
But keep up the good work these last few days
because just as fairies...

214
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:28,300
Queen Clarion! Queen Clarion!

215
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:30,900
Did I miss anything?

216
00:26:31,100 --> 00:26:34,500
- No, no, no.
- Good.

217
00:26:34,500 --> 00:26:36,900
It's alright.

218
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:40,700
I came up with some fantastic things for
Tinkers to use when we go to the Mainland.

219
00:26:43,700 --> 00:26:46,200
Let me show you.

220
00:26:47,200 --> 00:26:50,500
First, baby chipmunks can't eat the whole
nut, right?

221
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:54,400
Their little teeth can't chew big bites.

222
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:57,000
So, you just crank back this lever and its...

223
00:27:05,300 --> 00:27:09,000
Ups...

224
00:27:09,100 --> 00:27:12,500
It's kind of a work in progress!

225
00:27:12,500 --> 00:27:15,500
Yes, yes, yes, very clever.

226
00:27:15,500 --> 00:27:17,900
Oh, and I made this, too. It's a flower-sprayer.

227
00:27:18,000 --> 00:27:20,000
- Tinker Bell, I...
- Allow me to demonstrate!

228
00:27:30,100 --> 00:27:32,700
Sorry!!!

229
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:35,600
- But, but, wait till you see this last one!
- Tinker Bell!

230
00:27:35,700 --> 00:27:39,500
Sweetheart, has no one explained?

231
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:43,300
Explain what?

232
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:47,100
- Tinker fairies don't go to the Mainland, dear.
- What?

233
00:27:47,200 --> 00:27:50,200
All of those things are done by the Nature talent fairies!

234
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:53,900
