00:52:47,500 --> 00:52:50,500
It was me! I did it!

476
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:55,300
- It's all my fault!
- Tinker Bell!

477
00:52:55,300 --> 00:52:58,200
I'm sorry!

478
00:53:13,800 --> 00:53:18,400
I don't think we can fix this in time!
We're going to have to cancel spring!

479
00:53:18,500 --> 00:53:21,700
Or postpone it, to the very least!

480
00:53:22,700 --> 00:53:25,100
What? And put my fairies back to work?
But we can't, we can't do that! If...

481
00:53:25,200 --> 00:53:28,700
The snow isn't melted, the...

482
00:53:27,800 --> 00:53:30,900
And then in autumn, there will be
nothing to harvest!

483
00:53:31,000 --> 00:53:34,800
Spring must happen on time, or the
balance of nature will be undone!

484
00:53:34,800 --> 00:53:39,600
- There must be something we can do!
- Certainly this has happened before!

485
00:53:39,600 --> 00:53:42,200
- It has, did you ever hear of the Ice Age?
- Settle down! All of you!

486
00:53:42,300 --> 00:53:46,300
Fairy Mary, is it even possible to redo
everything in such a short time?

487
00:53:50,300 --> 00:53:53,800
- No!
- Oh, no!

488
00:53:53,900 --> 00:53:58,500
We were so close, now it's all gone!

489
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:02,200
Who's going to paint our leaves now?

490
00:54:02,700 --> 00:54:06,000
- Plants will never grow!
- No more hills covered in daffodils?

491
00:54:35,000 --> 00:54:40,000
- You're ok, Tink?
- Oh, yeah!

492
00:54:40,100 --> 00:54:43,000
Yeah, I'm fine!

493
00:54:43,000 --> 00:54:46,900
I just came hoping to get a quick refill!

494
00:54:47,000 --> 00:54:51,000
- I'm going away for a while.
- Oh, how long are you going to be gone?

495
00:54:51,100 --> 00:54:55,000
- Well, actually, forever!
- Forever? Well...

496
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:58,900
In that case...

497
00:54:58,900 --> 00:55:02,700
A double scoop!

498
00:55:02,800 --> 00:55:06,800
- Forever is a pretty long time, so I hear!
- Thanks, Terrence!

499
00:55:06,900 --> 00:55:11,500
- You know my name?
- Well, sure. Why wouldn't I?

500
00:55:11,600 --> 00:55:15,000
I don't know. I'm just a dust keeper guy.

501
00:55:15,100 --> 00:55:19,000
I'm not exactly seen as the most
important fairy in Pixie Hollow!

502
00:55:19,300 --> 00:55:23,600
Terrence, what are you talking about? You're
probably the most important one there is!

503
00:55:23,700 --> 00:55:27,200
Without you, no one would have any magic.

504
00:55:27,300 --> 00:55:29,800
Your talent makes who you are! You
should be proud of it!

505
00:55:29,800 --> 00:55:34,700
I am!

506
00:55:38,800 --> 00:55:41,900
I... I... I'd better get going!

507
00:56:16,800 --> 00:56:21,700
Oh, oh, hey, Cheese!

508
00:56:22,500 --> 00:56:27,700
Be proud of your talent! What talent?

509
00:56:27,700 --> 00:56:30,900
I couldn't even get these silly things to work!

510
00:56:42,000 --> 00:56:45,800
Aaa... Lost things!

511
00:56:58,900 --> 00:57:02,900
That's it!

512
00:57:09,800 --> 00:57:14,200
Attention, everyone!

513
00:57:14,200 --> 00:57:17,200
I'm afraid I have distressing news!

514
00:57:17,300 --> 00:57:21,300
There is no way spring can come on time!

515
00:57:21,400 --> 00:57:24,700
Months of work was lost.

516
00:57:24,800 --> 00:57:29,500
And it will take us months to restore it all.

517
00:57:29,600 --> 00:57:32,550
So when the ever blossom opens tomorrow,
I'm afraid we will not be going to the...

518
00:57:32,600 --> 00:57:36,400
Mainland for spring.

519
00:57:36,500 --> 00:57:39,500
Wait! I know how we can fix everything!

520
00:57:39,600 --> 00:57:43,200
Tinker Bell?

521
00:57:44,300 --> 00:57:47,800
- Tinker Bell, I don't think this is...
- Just hear me out.

522
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:51,000
Please!... You!

523
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:55,900
How long does it take you to paint a ladybug?

524
00:57:55,900 --> 00:57:59,800
I don't know. Ten, 15 minutes, I guess!

525
00:58:17,800 --> 00:58:21,700
See? We can build more!

526
00:58:21,800 --> 00:58:25,800
I can show you how! Making paints, gathering
seeds, we can do it all in no time!

527
00:58:25,800 --> 00:58:31,400
- We have to at least try!
- Wait! Are we going to listen to her?

528
00:58:31,500 --> 00:58:35,000
She's the reason we're in this mess in
the first place!

529
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:39,300
- But I can fix...
- Tinker Bell is going to save us,

530
00:58:39,300 --> 00:58:42,900
with her dopey little do-hickies!

531
00:58:42,900 --> 00:58:47,300
What is your problem, Vidia? Why do
you think you're so much better than me?

532
00:58:47,300 --> 00:58:51,000
I am better than you, sweetie, I didn't
ruin spring!

533
00:58:51,100 --> 00:58:55,000
At least now I'm trying to help! Have you
ever helped anyone besides yourself?

534
00:58:55,100 --> 00:58:59,500
Well, I tried to help you! Maybe I should have
told you to...

535
00:58:59,500 --> 00:59:02,400
... capture the hawk instead of the thistles!

536
00:59:08,800 --> 00:59:12,800
Perhaps Tinker Bell was not the only one responsible!

537
00:59:12,800 --> 00:59:17,500
It seems to me that your fast-flying talent is well
suited to chasing down...

538
00:59:17,600 --> 00:59:21,400
... each and everyone of the thistles!

539
00:59:21,400 --> 00:59:25,300
- Me?
- Yes. And I expect them all...

540
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:30,600
... to be returned to Neddlepoint Meadow as
soon as possible!

541
00:59:30,600 --> 00:59:33,400
But... but that could take forever!

542
00:59:33,500 --> 00:59:37,200
Then I suggest you get started!

543
00:59:42,800 --> 00:59:46,800
Now, Tinker Bell, are you sure you can do this?

544
00:59:48,900 --> 00:59:52,400
Yes!

545
00:59:52,500 --> 00:59:57,400
Because I'm a Tinker! It's who I am!

546
00:59:57,400 --> 01:00:02,700
And Tinkers fix things!

547
01:00:02,800 --> 01:00:06,800
But I can't do it alone!

548
01:00:06,800 --> 01:00:09,900
Command us, miss Bell!

549
01:00:09,900 --> 01:00:13,800
- I'll help!
- Show us how, Tink!

550
01:00:13,800 --> 01:00:16,900
- I'll help you!
- Me, too!

551
01:00:16,900 --> 01:00:20,000
Ok. Gather all the twigs you can, all different sizes!
And tree-saps, we need lots of that!

552
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:26,300
But most importantly, we need to find lost things!

553
01:00:35,200 --> 01:00:39,500
- Ok, what have you got?
- How about this?

554
01:00:39,500 --> 01:00:43,400
- Will this do?
- Can you use this fuzzy thing, miss Bell?

555
01:00:43,400 --> 01:00:46,000
- Oh, yeah!
- It's not fuzzy!

556
01:00:46,000 --> 01:00:50,400
- Yes, it is!
- No, it isn't!

557
01:00:48,800 --> 01:00:52,900
Twig! Hammer! Magnification, please!

558
01:00:52,900 --> 01:00:55,900
Thank you.

559
01:00:57,000 --> 01:01:00,500
And that's how you do it.

560
01:01:00,600 --> 01:01:04,200
Now what do you suppose that...

561
01:01:04,300 --> 01:01:08,700
- Aaa!
- Aaa!

562
01:01:08,800 --> 01:01:13,000
- Oh...
- Clunk!

563
01:01:13,000 --> 01:01:17,500
You smell funny!

564
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:21,700
- Oh!
- Uuu!

565
01:01:21,700 --> 01:01:24,900
- I saw it first!
- I bumped into it!

566
01:01:25,000 --> 01:01:29,200
Let's tie this off here... so you just
squeeze this.

567
01:01:29,300 --> 01:01:33,500
- Then let it go and...
- Aaa!

568
01:01:33,800 --> 01:01:38,100
See? Simple!

569
01:01:38,200 --> 01:01:42,000
Now, just put the berries in and we'll
have plenty of paint in no time!

570
01:01:58,200 --> 01:02:01,600
We did it!

571
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:21,200
Six, seven and eight.

572
01:02:29,200 --> 01:02:31,800
Ohhh!

573
01:03:15,800 --> 01:03:20,800
You did it, Tinker Bell! You saved spring!

574
01:03:21,500 --> 01:03:24,100
- We all did it.
- Queen Clarion!

575
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:28,200
- Can't Tink come with us to the Mainland?
- Yeah!

576
01:03:28,500 --> 01:03:32,600
- She's done so much for everyone!
- No, no, you guys, really!

577
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:36,900
- I don't need to go.
- Buttercup, it's what you wanted.

578
01:03:37,000 --> 01:03:41,500
It's ok! My work is here and I still have so
much to do.

579
01:03:41,500 --> 01:03:44,400
- Not here, you don't!
- But I...

580
01:03:44,500 --> 01:03:48,100
- No but!
- Surprise, miss Bell!

581
01:03:48,200 --> 01:03:52,500
We found your tiny dancer!

582
01:03:52,500 --> 01:03:55,800
Actually, I ran across this myself many
seasons ago!

583
01:03:55,900 --> 01:04:00,300
I didn't have a clue what it was or how
to fix it.

584
01:04:00,300 --> 01:04:04,800
You did, Tinker Bell! You are quite a rare
talent indeed!

585
01:04:04,900 --> 01:04:09,800
And I imagine there's a little girl out
there who's missing this.

586
01:04:10,300 --> 01:04:14,300
What do you mean? How...?

587
01:04:14,600 --> 01:04:19,500
I think that perhaps a certain Tinker fairy
might have a job to do afterall.

588
01:04:19,600 --> 01:04:23,100
- On the Mainland!
- You mean I...

589
01:04:25,100 --> 01:04:29,200
- I knew you can...
- Oh, Tink!

590
01:04:29,300 --> 01:04:31,800
- Oh, we can help, miss Bell!
- I'm strong!

591
01:04:31,800 --> 01:04:34,900
- Come on, we got to go right now!
- Thank you, your highness!

592
01:04:35,000 --> 01:04:38,900
- But how will I find who it belongs to?
- You'll know!

593
01:04:39,000 --> 01:04:43,400
Now, go!

594
01:04:49,500 --> 01:04:53,500
Thank you!

595
01:04:56,000 --> 01:05:01,000
Tink! Hey! Something to help you on the Mainland!

596
01:05:02,300 --> 01:05:05,900
Oh, Terrence, that's so sweet!

597
01:05:06,000 --> 01:05:09,800
- Good luck, Tink!
- To the air, fairies!

598
01:05:09,900 --> 01:05:14,000
To the air! The Mainland awaits.

599
01:05:15,000 --> 01:05:19,400
Come away with me now, to the sky.

600
01:05:19,400 --> 01:05:23,400
Up on the hills and the sea,

601
01:05:23,500 --> 01:05:26,800
Far beyond, where memories lie,

602
01:05:26,900 --> 01:05:31,300
To a place where I'm free to believe!

603
01:05:35,300 --> 01:05:39,400
Oh, can you hear them all,

604
01:05:39,400 --> 01:05:42,800
No matter what Polly may do?

605
01:05:42,900 --> 01:05:47,500
Let the stars fill us all,

606
01:05:47,500 --> 01:05:52,800
And the moon craddle the soul,
So to yourself be true!

607
01:05:55,300 --> 01:06:02,500
The blanket of snow is so cold,

608
01:06:02,600 --> 01:06:08,000
Each flower waits for the sun
And the blissful tears of the rain!

609
01:06:08,000 --> 01:06:13,300
It's a promise for everyone!

610
01:06:13,700 --> 01:06:17,300
Then come away with me, friends,

611
01:06:17,300 --> 01:06:20,800
No matter where you come from!

612
01:06:20,900 --> 01:06:26,200
With a light in our hearts,
We will never part,

613
01:06:26,400 --> 01:06:31,400
- No matter how far we go!
- Fairies to the South! To the East and West!

614
01:06:42,400 --> 01:06:48,300
Deep in the forrest we go!

615
01:06:48,300 --> 01:06:52,800
- Wake up, sleepy heads!
- Creatures are all fast asleep!

616
01:06:52,900 --> 01:06:57,000
With a kiss and a grim we will wake

617
01:06:57,400 --> 01:07:02,500
And always in safety we'll keep.

618
01:07:02,600 --> 01:07:07,600
And then we'll dance to the light,
To the sun sparkles at dawn.

619
01:07:07,600 --> 01:07:11,800
And away we will go
Like the last winter snow,

620
01:07:12,300 --> 01:07:16,500
Soon our work will be done!

621
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:20,500
Oh, come with me you all!

622
01:07:20,600 --> 01:07:24,900
No matter wht Polly may do!

623
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:33,500
So to yourself be true!

624
01:07:46,500 --> 01:07:50,200
Oh, come with me now you all,

625
01:07:50,500 --> 01:07:54,400
No matter what Polly may do!

626
01:07:54,500 --> 01:07:58,400
Let the stars fill us all
And the moon cradle the soul!

627
01:07:58,500 --> 01:08:03,300
So to yourself be true!

628
01:08:11,300 --> 01:08:16,100
So to yourself be true!

629
01:09:23,800 --> 01:09:27,000
Aaa!

630
01:09:46,200 --> 01:09:49,200
Aaa!

631
01:10:11,800 --> 01:10:16,400
Mommy! Guess what?

632
01:10:16,500 --> 01:10:20,500
- Guess what?
- Yes, Wendy, what is it, darling?

633
01:10:26,700 --> 01:10:30,800
A fairy's work is much more than
at first it might appear!

634
01:10:30,900 --> 01:10:35,700
Suppose your broken clock ticks,
though it hasn't in a year!

635
01:10:35,800 --> 01:10:40,000
Perchance you found a toy you lost or
gingling bells you hear!

636
01:10:43,200 --> 01:10:47,900
It all means that one very special fairy...

637
01:10:48,000 --> 01:10:52,400
... might be near!

